      "text": [
        " : قُلْتُ لِأَبِي عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ رَجُلٌ أَقَرَّ أَنَّهُ عَبْدٌ قَالَ يَأْخُذُهُ بِمَا قَالَ أَوْ يَرُدَّ اَلْمَالَ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3516 - Al-'Abbas ibn 'Amir narrated from Aban, from Muhammad ibn al-Fadl al-Hashimi, who said:\n\"I said to Abu Abdullah (as), 'A man admitted that he is a slave.'\nImam (as) said: 'He will be held accountable based on what he said, or he must return the wealth.'\""
        ]
      }
    },
